title: Advance Senior SIGINT Analystt
description: 2011-2013 Advance Collection Team, U.S Army 7th Special Forces Group (A), EGLIN AFB, FL Served as a Senior Signals Intelligence/Electronic Warfare (SIGINT/EW) Cryptologic Linguist and collection equipment operator in the Technical Control and Analysis Element (TCAE) for the 7th Special Forces Group (Airborne) operating in the CENTCOM and SOUTHCOM Areas of Operations; Assists with technical, analytical and linguistic support for 7th Special Forces Group (Airborne) primary areas of operations. - Provided numerous training with peers to ensure they were trained proficiently in tactical ground equipment; UHF/HF/VHF/Wolfhound System/PRD-13 System/DRT1500 box. - Trained with TICOM Geometrics on GEONET software while still in its testing phase and development. - Trained and became qualified on Counter Electronic Warfare Systems during a three week Electronic Warfare Maintainer course.

summary: Active Top Secret/ SCI clearance with HCS/Gamma Provided Through Single Scope Background Investigation (SSBI). I have completed 8 years SIGINT analyst performance in different Areas of Operations. Skilled Intelligence Analyst with Tactical/Strategic organizational, analytical, and training abilities. Provided SIGINT support to Coalition Force elements through 24-hour watch operations. Utilized numerous IC databases and tipping tools to yield a number of reports daily. Experience in OEF extends to; Low Level Voice Interception (LLVI), Signal Terminal Guidance (STG), numerous program and various SIGINT databases search engines and disciplines. Task Force 3-10 Geospatial analysis while assisting the Tactical Screening Facility, ISR support and Air coordinations, Task-Force 3-10 target development. SIGINT analysis stateside as well as leading elements while providing (STG) SIGINT terminal guidance/VHF ground guidance to overseas in a high stress environment. My first deployment, as a SIGINT Analyst, I was the training NCOIC for the foreign soldiers, late comers to the deployment and anyone who needed assistance fixing equipment, configuring databases/or tools, as well as report- writing / Mission tasking / de-tasking priorities, while supporting air assets during combat operations. I was awarded the Army Joint Service Commendation Medal for my work as a Senior SIGINT Analyst, specifically, for providing accurate information during Combat Operations and preventing attacks to Forces. Completed two rotations to Afghanistan (OEF) as a Senior-Level Ground SIGINT Analyst Operator, and Geospatial Analyst for target development in 2009 and 2010. Additionally, I participated in numerous Objectives providing SIGINT/EW support to Task-Force Commander capturing and neutralizing many OBJs while developing new target packages.

title: Senior SIGINT Analyst (Linguist)
company: Senior Cryptologic Linguist, 75th Ranger Regiment, Ft Benning, GA
description: 2009-2011 Senior Cryptologic Linguist, 75th Ranger Regiment, Ft Benning, GA Senior Cryptologic SIGINT Linguist for a globally deployable tactical Operational SIGINT Team (OST) which conducts Signals Intelligence (SIGINT) and Electronic Warfare (EW) operations in support of the 75th Ranger Regiment Special Troops Battalion and the three Ranger Line Battalions; responsible for exploitation and analysis of communication devices; which conducts SIGINT/EW and radio reconnaissance operations in denied, hostile, and politically sensitive areas; responsible for all linguistic duties for languages in Central and South America; responsible for operational training for the CENTCOM areas of Operations. - Received Army impact award for numerous Tactical combat Operation. - Produced numerous SIGINT reports in response to Request for information from Task Force personnel resulting in the detainment of numerous High Value Targets. - Led SIGINT Team in numerous tactical Objectives who... - Worked as the Geospatial SIGINT Analyst Exploitation NCOIC for a Tactical Screening Facility; CELLEX, DOCEX section. - Conducted Task Force SIGINT daily briefings, Analysis, Target Development, Tactical equipment training, and Mission Support during tactical deployment during Operation Enduring Freedom (OEF).

title: Senior SIGINT Analyst (Linguist)

summary: Active Top Secret/ SCI clearance with HCS/Gamma Provided Through Single Scope Background Investigation (SSBI). I have completed 8 years SIGINT analyst performance in different Areas of Operations. Skilled Intelligence Analyst with Tactical/Strategic organizational, analytical, and training abilities. Provided SIGINT support to Coalition Force elements through 24-hour watch operations. Utilized numerous IC databases and tipping tools to yield a number of reports daily. Experience in OEF extends to; Low Level Voice Interception (LLVI), Signal Terminal Guidance (STG), numerous program and various SIGINT databases search engines and disciplines. Task Force 3-10 Geospatial analysis while assisting the Tactical Screening Facility, ISR support and Air coordinations, Task-Force 3-10 target development. SIGINT analysis stateside as well as leading elements while providing (STG) SIGINT terminal guidance/VHF ground guidance to overseas in a high stress environment. My first deployment, as a SIGINT Analyst, I was the training NCOIC for the foreign soldiers, late comers to the deployment and anyone who needed assistance fixing equipment, configuring databases/or tools, as well as report- writing / Mission tasking / de-tasking priorities, while supporting air assets during combat operations. I was awarded the Army Joint Service Commendation Medal for my work as a Senior SIGINT Analyst, specifically, for providing accurate information during Combat Operations and preventing attacks to Forces. Completed two rotations to Afghanistan (OEF) as a Senior-Level Ground SIGINT Analyst Operator, and Geospatial Analyst for target development in 2009 and 2010. Additionally, I participated in numerous Objectives providing SIGINT/EW support to Task-Force Commander capturing and neutralizing many OBJs while developing new target packages.

summary: A diverse background consisting of more than 21 years in law enforcement which has included fulfilling duties as a bomb technician, an explosive detection canine handler, and a lead instructor tasked with educating 318 municipalities' police/fire personnel, scholastic institutions/administrations and private companies across the Commonwealth in the topics of explosives and response to explosive incidents. In the ninth year of my law enforcement career I enlisted as a member of the Army National Guard and soon after became a member of the U.S. Army Special Forces Regiment. I currently have 8 years of experience assigned to various operational detachments as the senior Special Forces Engineer and currently as the Intelligence Sergeant/18F. I have broad experience participating in the planning and execution of combat operations (encompassing CI/HUMINT/SIGINT collection activities and their fusion with operations) in both Iraq and Afghanistan. Focused experience working as an intelligence analyst in support of the Counter-IED mission in Afghanistan. Demonstrated proficiency: conducting Counter Intelligence operations to enhance force protection in combat environments; in the collection and use of biometrics in the targeting process; collection and preservation of evidence in support of criminal prosecution; utilizing SIPRNET & JWICS search engines (CIDNE; M3; WebTAS; COIC tools; DCGS-A; i2 Analyst Notebook; ArcGIS) for data collection, analysis and intelligence product production. Seeking full-time employment. Current TS/SCI. I am willing to relocate if necessary. Complete resume available upon request.

title: 18C - Senior Special Forces Engineer
description: -Performed, supervised and instructed engineer techniques and operations while employed in conventional and unconventional warfare operational areas -Responsible for ensuring the Detachment is updated in current enemy Tactics, Techniques and Procedures, (TTPs) involving the use of Improvised Explosive Devices, (IEDs) employed against Coalition Forces, (CF) in the Afghanistan Theater of Operation, and other countries our unit may be deployed -Performed duties of S4, Supply NCO for the 12-man Detachment maintaining accountability of all organic team equipment -Maintained Range Safety Officer certification in order to facilitate Detachment training requirements while also building and implementing an explosives range program of instruction (POI) -Maintained a high level of physical fitness in order to remain an effective operational team member capable of fulfilling mission requirements in any possible environment -Remained proficient in all Detachment operational specialties through regular cross-training with trauma medicine, communications equipment and weapons -Maintained foreign language proficiency in target area languages as directed (French, Arabic) -As the Detachments Antiterrorism Officer, I was responsible for maintaining and advising team members regarding all matters of force protection in order to ensure facility and operational security in any environment to include compliance with Department of the Army regulations

description: -Primary duties involved the preparation of Special Assessments and Field Summary Analysis products, TTP analysis, review daily and weekly Executive Summaries/ Intelligence Summaries/ Graphic Intelligence Summaries from across the Afghanistan Theater of Operation (ATO) -Daily analysis of Level I Explosive Ordnance Disposal (EOD) reports from assigned areas of operation and apply knowledge and experience to Weapons Technical Intelligence (WTI) and Network analysis -Using WTI data, routinely responded to Requests for Information (RFI) from Battle Space Owners, Combatant Commanders, CJTF Paladin and other requestors -Supported Theater Explosive Exploitation (TEX) Military Intelligence personnel, Operations personnel and the Officer in Charge -Monitored EOD Level I reporting and validate Level II Exploitation as well as forensic and biometric intelligence data -Performed Level I & II WTI analysis of insurgent devices and TTP's for pattern, trend and TTP analysis of IED devices and captures for comprehensive analytical products -Provided TECHINT analysis in order to associate like IED devices based on builder signature. -Published Special Assessments and provided analysis of CBRNE related captured enemy materials; supported analysis of captured enemy devices and materials and provided explosive device damage assessments. -Responsible for briefing the TEX chain of command weekly regarding high profile attacks/incidents and new trends. -Briefed incoming EOD teams regarding past and present enemy TTPs. -Worked daily with coalition partners responsible for the administration of the Multi-National Technical Exploitation Lab, (MNTEL-Kabul) in order to maintain continuity of evidence collection in areas of Afghanistan having little or no US EOD asset presence. -Provided weekly Theater-wide IED analysis product to TF 310 EOD Officer and NCOIC -Demonstrated proficiency in the use of WebTAS, CIDNE, WEAT, COIC tools and their interface with Microsoft products.

summary: A diverse background consisting of more than 21 years in law enforcement which has included fulfilling duties as a bomb technician, an explosive detection canine handler, and a lead instructor tasked with educating 318 municipalities' police/fire personnel, scholastic institutions/administrations and private companies across the Commonwealth in the topics of explosives and response to explosive incidents. In the ninth year of my law enforcement career I enlisted as a member of the Army National Guard and soon after became a member of the U.S. Army Special Forces Regiment. I currently have 8 years of experience assigned to various operational detachments as the senior Special Forces Engineer and currently as the Intelligence Sergeant/18F. I have broad experience participating in the planning and execution of combat operations (encompassing CI/HUMINT/SIGINT collection activities and their fusion with operations) in both Iraq and Afghanistan. Focused experience working as an intelligence analyst in support of the Counter-IED mission in Afghanistan. Demonstrated proficiency: conducting Counter Intelligence operations to enhance force protection in combat environments; in the collection and use of biometrics in the targeting process; collection and preservation of evidence in support of criminal prosecution; utilizing SIPRNET & JWICS search engines (CIDNE; M3; WebTAS; COIC tools; DCGS-A; i2 Analyst Notebook; ArcGIS) for data collection, analysis and intelligence product production. Seeking full-time employment. Current TS/SCI. I am willing to relocate if necessary. Complete resume available upon request.

title: Senior Bomb Technician
company: MSP Bomb Squad / Massachusetts Port Authority
description: -Provided emergency response throughout a category X, international airport to any incident involving the threat or use of explosives, explosive devices, chemical, biological, radiological or nuclear substances/agents as a member of a 7-man unit constisting of 6 certified bomb technicians and one sergeant -Assisted DHS Transportation and Security Administration with the identification and mitigation of explosive hazards which may have adversely affected air travel by providing 24 hour response to TSA checkpoints and baggage inspection rooms for alarm resolution -Provided instruction to the various departments within the Massachusetts Port Authority to include Fire/EMS and state police personnel in the safe response and resolution of explosive related incidents -Developed and implemented on the job training plans in order to further the training of less experienced bomb technicians -Maintained and utilized Explosive Ordnance Disposal equipment such as various robotic platforms manufactured by Remotec, Foster Miller, and iRobot, various types of bomb disposal suits, disrupters, CBRNE enhanced total containment vessels, response vehicles and various types of high explosives. -Maintained proficiency in the use of explosives relating to render safe procedures and explosive breaching. -Worked closely with various federal, state and local law enforcement agencies in order to investigate and/or resolve any terrorist or criminal incident involving the threat or actual use of explosives. -Coordinated, supervised and performed dignitary protection sweeps in conjunction with the US Secret Service, US Department of State-Diplomatic Security Service, Military EOD technicians and explosive detection canine teams

summary: A diverse background consisting of more than 21 years in law enforcement which has included fulfilling duties as a bomb technician, an explosive detection canine handler, and a lead instructor tasked with educating 318 municipalities' police/fire personnel, scholastic institutions/administrations and private companies across the Commonwealth in the topics of explosives and response to explosive incidents. In the ninth year of my law enforcement career I enlisted as a member of the Army National Guard and soon after became a member of the U.S. Army Special Forces Regiment. I currently have 8 years of experience assigned to various operational detachments as the senior Special Forces Engineer and currently as the Intelligence Sergeant/18F. I have broad experience participating in the planning and execution of combat operations (encompassing CI/HUMINT/SIGINT collection activities and their fusion with operations) in both Iraq and Afghanistan. Focused experience working as an intelligence analyst in support of the Counter-IED mission in Afghanistan. Demonstrated proficiency: conducting Counter Intelligence operations to enhance force protection in combat environments; in the collection and use of biometrics in the targeting process; collection and preservation of evidence in support of criminal prosecution; utilizing SIPRNET & JWICS search engines (CIDNE; M3; WebTAS; COIC tools; DCGS-A; i2 Analyst Notebook; ArcGIS) for data collection, analysis and intelligence product production. Seeking full-time employment. Current TS/SCI. I am willing to relocate if necessary. Complete resume available upon request.

title: Senior SF Engineer
description: Operation Iraqi Freedom Senior SF Engineer Sergeant 10/2005 – 09/2006 POC: SGM Kent Brewer (Ret.) 850-997-0255 • Worked as the sole engineer assigned to a 6-man element while also performing the duties of a Weapons Sergeant and a Communications Sergeant due to limited team assets • Cross trained the Detachment and team attachments in the safe and proper use of explosives, UXO (Unexploded Ordnance) clearance and explosive breaching • Worked as Human Intelligence Collector and Analyst operating in an area encompassing the southern half of Iraq in support of ISOF/ICTF operations, local force protection, Counter-Intelligence operations, • The Detachment trained, mentored and lead 11-man Iraqi Special Operations Force, (ISOF) element for employment in combined kinetic operations both in the city of Ad Diwaniyah and other major southern cities • Trained and advised ISOF element in Close Target Reconnaissance (CTR) • Conducted firearms and Close Quarters Combat training for the 15-man Diwaniyah SWAT team in conjunction with members of the Polish Special Forces • Conducted Close Quarters Combat training for two Company sized elements of the 8th Iraqi Army in order to conduct kinetic combat operations in the local Area of Operation • Assumed the duties of the Detachment Field Ordering Officer overseeing the expenditure of operational funds in excess of 60,000 USD resulting in zero deficiencies • Assisted U.S. Navy EOD unit with post blast analysis operations involving Coalition Force casualties along MSR Tampa; also assisted with UXO clearance operations throughout southern Iraq • Conducted multiple operations in conjunction with the Italian Special Forces in An Naseriyah resulting in the recovery and destruction of over 500kg of explosive materials permanently removed from the battlefield successfully reducing the IED threat on MSR Tampa

summary: A diverse background consisting of more than 21 years in law enforcement which has included fulfilling duties as a bomb technician, an explosive detection canine handler, and a lead instructor tasked with educating 318 municipalities' police/fire personnel, scholastic institutions/administrations and private companies across the Commonwealth in the topics of explosives and response to explosive incidents. In the ninth year of my law enforcement career I enlisted as a member of the Army National Guard and soon after became a member of the U.S. Army Special Forces Regiment. I currently have 8 years of experience assigned to various operational detachments as the senior Special Forces Engineer and currently as the Intelligence Sergeant/18F. I have broad experience participating in the planning and execution of combat operations (encompassing CI/HUMINT/SIGINT collection activities and their fusion with operations) in both Iraq and Afghanistan. Focused experience working as an intelligence analyst in support of the Counter-IED mission in Afghanistan. Demonstrated proficiency: conducting Counter Intelligence operations to enhance force protection in combat environments; in the collection and use of biometrics in the targeting process; collection and preservation of evidence in support of criminal prosecution; utilizing SIPRNET & JWICS search engines (CIDNE; M3; WebTAS; COIC tools; DCGS-A; i2 Analyst Notebook; ArcGIS) for data collection, analysis and intelligence product production. Seeking full-time employment. Current TS/SCI. I am willing to relocate if necessary. Complete resume available upon request.

title: Bomb Technician / EDC K9 Handler
company: MSP Bomb Squad / Office of the State Fire Marshal
description: -Provided 24 hour response capability throughout the Commonwealth to incidents involving the threat or use of explosives, explosive devices (IEDs), chemical, biological, radiological or nuclear substances and/or devices as part of a 7-man unit consisting of 6 certified bomb technicians and one sergeant -Administered training as a lead instructor to first responders from municipalities throughout the Commonwealth on the safe response and handling of incidents involving the threat or use of explosives, or explosive devices and their components to include instruction regarding the understanding of the effects of explosives and explosive devices, recognition, means of employment and search procedures -Conducted training seminars for public/private school systems and Fortune 500 companies in the safe response and handling of explosive related incidents -Testified as an expert witness in various bombing investigations involving murder, attempted murder, and malicious destruction of property -Maintained a food reward, explosive detection canine requiring daily training, quarterly proficiency testing and yearly chemist certification in order to remain proficient for employment in confirming or denying the presence of explosives in the event of bomb threats and security sweeps -Planned, coordinated and performed dignitary protection sweeps in conjunction with local, state and federal agencies to include, but not limited to the United State Secret Service, DoS Diplomatic Security Service and the Department of Homeland Security -Provided EOD/K9 support to all major events occuring within the Commonwealth and neighboring states such as New Hampshire, Vermont and Rhode Island in support of the yearly Governors' Conference, July 4th Boston Esplanade Celebration, Sail-Boston 2000, OpSail-Boston 2012, Westover AFB Air Show, the 1998 Ryder Cup and all major events at Patriot's (Gillette) Stadium
